result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Zachary T. Blahnik in court with attorney Jessica L Schuster.  Defendant Zachary T. Blahnik in custody.  Elizabeth R. Constable appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 17CF62, 16CF165, 16CF99, 16CF3, 16CF50, 16CF87, 16CF44 @ 11:32 a.m. Agreement stated - 17CF62 Def will plead to ct 1, 2, 3, dri cts 4-9, 16CF165 - move to dri, 16CF99 Def will plead to ct 1, dri cts 2-6. 16CF87 Def will plead to ct 1, 16CF50 dri cts 1, 2, & 3. 16CF44 dri cts 1 & 2, 16CF3 dri ct 1. 17CF62 ct 1 - 18 months initial confinement, 2 yrs ext supv, ct 2 - 18 mo ic, 2 yrs ext supv, concurrent to ct 1, ct 3 - 3 yrs ic, 3 yrs ext supv, concurrent. 16CF99 ct 1 - 1 yr ic, 2 yrs ext supv consecutive to  16CF87 - 1 yr ic, 2 yrs ext supv., concurrent to all other sentences. Court costs, DNA, counseling as deemed necessary by DOC on all. All sentence credit applied to 16CF99 - stipulate 96 days. Def agrees with stated agreement. Waiver of prelim reviewed with Def. Court finds waivers knowing and voluntary and finds probable cause on 17CF62, 16CF99 and 16CF187 and binds over. Informations filed. Reading waived. Plea quest. reviewed. 17CF62 ct  - no contest plea, ct 2 no contest, ct 3 no contest. 16CF99 ct 1 - no contest plea. 16CF87 ct 1 - no contest plea. Court grants motion to dismiss and read in 17CF62 cts 4-9, 16CF165 ct 1, 16CF99 cts 2-6, 16CF3 ct 1, 16CF50 cts 1-3, 16CF44 cts 1 & 2. State has complied with victim rights. No restitution. Constitutional rights, elements, (Def admits prior convictions) possible penalties reviewed. Atty Schuster satisfied. Court finds Def understands and pleas freely & voluntarily made. Factual basis. Court accepts pleas and finds Def guilty of 17CF62 cts 1, 2 & 3, 16CF99 ct 1, and 16CF87 ct 1. Sentencing remarks by Counsel. Statement by Defendant. Remarks by the Court. Will follow agreement.
17CF62 ct 1 - 3 1/2 yrs prison, 1 1/2 yrs  initial confinement, 2 yrs extended supervision, court costs, DNA. Ct 2 - 3 1/2 yrs prison, 18 months initial, 2 yrs ext supv, Court costs, DNA surcharge. concurrent to ct 1. Ct 3 - 6 yrs prison, 3 yrs initial, 3 yrs ext supv.Court costs, DNA surcharge. Concurrent.
16CF99 ct 1 - 3 yrs prison, 1 yr initial, 2 yrs ext supv. Consecutive to 17CF62. Court costs, DNA surcharge. All ext supervision - condition - counseling and assessments as deemed necessary. 96 days credit on 16CF99.
16CF87 ct 1 - 3 yrs prison, 1 yr inital, 2 yrs ext supv. Court costs. DNA surcharge. Concurrent to 17CF62.  Bond in 16CF50 forfeited to County. 
Def advised of firearms and voting restrictions. Def eligible for CIP and substance abuse programs. DNA sample. Postconviction rights.

Court calls 16CF3, 16CF44, 16CF50, 16CF87, 16CF99 & 16CF165 @ 1:36 pm.  Defendant Zachary T. Blahnik in court, in custody & via-video, Atty Schuster attorney special appears .  Jill Louise Laufenberg appeared for the State of Wisconsin. State heard on bond recommendation. 16CF87, 16CF3, 16CF44 & 16CF50 State moves to forfeit bond.  Not sure on child support case.  Atty Schuster gives statement.  16CF165 Atty Schuster has copy of complaint, waives reading.  Waives time limits on all cases. Court orders $5,000 cash bond to cover all 6 cases.  Def. questions all cases.  Atty Schuster will provide copies to def. Def. waives time limits for p.h. Court accepts waiver time limits on 16CF165. 16CF99 State moves to forfeit bond.  All bonds to be forfeited pending hearing on all cases with bond.  Status conference scheduled for May 1, 2017 at 03:30 pm.

Court calls  16CF44, 16CF99, 16CF87, 16CF50, & 16CF3 @ 1:20 pm.  Defendant Zachary T. Blahnik not in court.  Elizabeth R. Constable appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court orders body only warrant on all cases - Statewide.  State does not object.
